91 /**
92  * @brief Helper function for CANTX_CellTemperatures()
93  *
94  * Used in the CANTX_CellTemperatures() callback to set
95  * invalid flag data and temperature data
96  * in the CAN frame.
97  *
98  * @param[in] muxId multiplexer value
99  * @param[in] pMessage pointer to CAN frame data
100  * @param[in] cellTemperatureSignal signal characteristics for temperature data
101  * @param[in] cellTemperatureInvalidFlagSignal signal characteristics for invalid flag data
102  * @param[in] endianness big or little endianness of data
103  * @param[in] kpkCanShim shim to the database entries
104  */
105 static void CANTX_TemperatureSetData(
106  uint8_t muxId,
107  uint64_t *pMessage,
108  CAN_SIGNAL_TYPE_s cellTemperatureSignal,
109  CAN_SIGNAL_TYPE_s cellTemperatureInvalidFlagSignal,
110  CAN_ENDIANNESS_e endianness,
111  const CAN_SHIM_s *const kpkCanShim);
112 
113 /*========== Static Function Implementations ================================*/
114 
115 static void CANTX_TemperatureSetData(
116  uint8_t muxId,
117  uint64_t *pMessage,
118  CAN_SIGNAL_TYPE_s cellTemperatureSignal,
119  CAN_SIGNAL_TYPE_s cellTemperatureInvalidFlagSignal,
120  CAN_ENDIANNESS_e endianness,
121  const CAN_SHIM_s *const kpkCanShim) {
122  /* sensor index must not be greater than the number of sensors */
123  if (muxId < BS_NR_OF_TEMP_SENSORS) {
124  /* start_index end_index module
125  * 00 17 module1
126  * 18 35 module2
127  * 20 53 module3
128  * 30 71 module4
129  */
130  /* start_index end_index string
131  * 000 071 string0
132  */
133 
134  /* Get string, module and cell number */
135  const uint8_t stringNumber = DATA_GetStringNumberFromTemperatureIndex(muxId);
136  const uint8_t moduleNumber = DATA_GetModuleNumberFromTemperatureIndex(muxId);
137  const uint8_t sensorNumber = DATA_GetSensorNumberFromTemperatureIndex(muxId);
138 
139  uint32_t signalData_valid;
140  /* Valid bits data */
141  if ((kpkCanShim->pTableCellTemperature->invalidCellTemperature[stringNumber][moduleNumber] &
142  (1u << sensorNumber)) == 0u) {
143  signalData_valid = 0u;
144  } else {
145  signalData_valid = 1u;
146  }
147  /* Set valid bit data in CAN frame */
148  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
149  pMessage,
150  cellTemperatureInvalidFlagSignal.bitStart,
151  cellTemperatureInvalidFlagSignal.bitLength,
152  signalData_valid,
153  endianness);
154 
155  /* Temperature data */
156  float_t signalData_degC =
157  (float_t)kpkCanShim->pTableCellTemperature
158  ->cellTemperature_ddegC[stringNumber][(moduleNumber * BS_NR_OF_TEMP_SENSORS_PER_MODULE) + sensorNumber];
159  signalData_degC /= UNIT_CONVERSION_FACTOR_10_FLOAT; /* Convert temperature from decidegC to degC */
160  /* Apply offset and factor, check min/max limits */
161  CAN_TxPrepareSignalData(&signalData_degC, cellTemperatureSignal);
162  /* Set temperature data in CAN frame */
163  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
164  pMessage,
165  cellTemperatureSignal.bitStart,
166  cellTemperatureSignal.bitLength,
167  (int32_t)signalData_degC,
168  endianness);
169  }
170 }
171 
172 /*========== Extern Function Implementations ================================*/
173 extern uint32_t CANTX_CellTemperatures(
174  CAN_MESSAGE_PROPERTIES_s message,
175  uint8_t *pCanData,
176  uint8_t *pMuxId,
177  const CAN_SHIM_s *const kpkCanShim) {
178  FAS_ASSERT(message.id == CANTX_CELL_TEMPERATURES_ID);
179  FAS_ASSERT(message.idType == CANTX_CELL_TEMPERATURES_ID_TYPE);
180  FAS_ASSERT(message.dlc == CAN_FOXBMS_MESSAGES_DEFAULT_DLC);
181  FAS_ASSERT(pCanData != NULL_PTR);
182  FAS_ASSERT(pMuxId != NULL_PTR);
183  FAS_ASSERT(kpkCanShim != NULL_PTR);
184  uint64_t messageData = 0u;
185 
186  /* Reset mux if maximum was reached */
187  if (*pMuxId >= BS_NR_OF_TEMP_SENSORS) {
188  *pMuxId = 0u;
189  }
190 
191  /* first signal to transmit cell voltages: get database values */
192  if (*pMuxId == 0u) {
193  DATA_READ_DATA(kpkCanShim->pTableCellTemperature);
194  }
195 
196  /* Set mux signal in CAN frame */
197  uint32_t signalData = *pMuxId / 6u; /* 6 temperatures per module */
198  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
199  &messageData,
200  cantx_cellTemperatureMultiplexer.bitStart,
201  cantx_cellTemperatureMultiplexer.bitLength,
202  signalData,
203  message.endianness);
204 
205  /* Set other signals in CAN frame */
206  /* Each temperature frame contains 6 temperatures, with a correspond invalid flag*/
207  CANTX_TemperatureSetData(
208  *pMuxId,
209  &messageData,
210  cantx_cell0Temperature_degC,
211  cantx_cell0TemperatureInvalidFlag,
212  message.endianness,
213  kpkCanShim);
214  /* Increment multiplexer for next cell */
215  (*pMuxId)++;
216  CANTX_TemperatureSetData(
217  *pMuxId,
218  &messageData,
219  cantx_cell1Temperature_degC,
220  cantx_cell1TemperatureInvalidFlag,
221  message.endianness,
222  kpkCanShim);
223  /* Increment multiplexer for next cell */
224  (*pMuxId)++;
225  CANTX_TemperatureSetData(
226  *pMuxId,
227  &messageData,
228  cantx_cell2Temperature_degC,
229  cantx_cell2TemperatureInvalidFlag,
230  message.endianness,
231  kpkCanShim);
232  /* Increment multiplexer for next cell */
233  (*pMuxId)++;
234  CANTX_TemperatureSetData(
235  *pMuxId,
236  &messageData,
237  cantx_cell3Temperature_degC,
238  cantx_cell3TemperatureInvalidFlag,
239  message.endianness,
240  kpkCanShim);
241  /* Increment multiplexer for next cell */
242  (*pMuxId)++;
243  CANTX_TemperatureSetData(
244  *pMuxId,
245  &messageData,
246  cantx_cell4Temperature_degC,
247  cantx_cell4TemperatureInvalidFlag,
248  message.endianness,
249  kpkCanShim);
250  /* Increment multiplexer for next cell */
251  (*pMuxId)++;
252  CANTX_TemperatureSetData(
253  *pMuxId,
254  &messageData,
255  cantx_cell5Temperature_degC,
256  cantx_cell5TemperatureInvalidFlag,
257  message.endianness,
258  kpkCanShim);
259  /* Increment multiplexer for next cell */
260  (*pMuxId)++;
261 
262  /* All signal data copied in CAN frame, now copy data in the buffer that will be use to send the frame */
263  CAN_TxSetCanDataWithMessageData(messageData, pCanData, message.endianness);
264 
265  return 0;
266 }
